{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1370,"text":"This is Charley Williams."},{"time":3111,"text":"He was 94 when this photograph was taken."},{"time":5387,"text":"In the 1930s, Roosevelt put"},{"time":8444,"text":"thousands and thousands of Americans back to work"},{"time":10424,"text":"by building bridges and infrastructure and tunnels,"},{"time":12950,"text":"but he also did something interesting,"},{"time":14365,"text":"which was to hire a few hundred writers"},{"time":16677,"text":"to scour America to capture the stories of ordinary Americans."},{"time":20638,"text":"Charley Williams, a poor sharecropper,"},{"time":22799,"text":"wouldn't ordinarily be the subject of a big interview,"},{"time":25461,"text":"but Charley had actually been a slave"},{"time":27889,"text":"until he was 22 years old."},{"time":30447,"text":"And the stories that were captured of his life"},{"time":32761,"text":"make up one of the crown jewels"},{"time":35540,"text":"of histories, of human-lived experiences"},{"time":38865,"text":"filled with ex-slaves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41140,"text":"Anna Deavere Smith famously said that"},{"time":43240,"text":"there's a literature inside of each of us,"},{"time":45728,"text":"and three generations later, I was part of a project"},{"time":47991,"text":"called StoryCorps,"},{"time":49552,"text":"which set out to capture"},{"time":51544,"text":"the stories of ordinary Americans"},{"time":53569,"text":"by setting up a soundproof booth in public spaces."},{"time":56466,"text":"The idea is very, very simple."},{"time":57696,"text":"You go into these booths, you interview your grandmother"},{"time":60567,"text":"or relative, you leave with a copy of the interview"},{"time":62855,"text":"and an interview goes into the Library of Congress."},{"time":65642,"text":"It's essentially a way to make a national oral histories archive"},{"time":69000,"text":"one conversation at a time."},{"time":71272,"text":"And the question is, who do you want to remember --"},{"time":73746,"text":"if you had just 45 minutes with your grandmother?"},{"time":76818,"text":"What's interesting, in conversations with the founder, Dave Isay,"},{"time":79190,"text":"we always actually talked about this"},{"time":80338,"text":"as a little bit of a subversive project,"},{"time":82588,"text":"because when you think about it,"},{"time":83989,"text":"it's actually not really about the stories that are being told,"},{"time":86505,"text":"it's about listening,"},{"time":87811,"text":"and it's about the questions that you get to ask,"},{"time":89845,"text":"questions that you may not have permission to"},{"time":91923,"text":"on any other day."},{"time":93193,"text":"I'm going to play you just a couple of quick excerpts from the project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98131,"text":"[Jesus Melendez talking about poet Pedro Pietri's final moments]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":100109,"text":"Jesus Melendez: We took off, and as we were ascending,"},{"time":102675,"text":"before we had leveled off,"},{"time":104318,"text":"our level-off point was 45,000 feet,"},{"time":106747,"text":"so before we had leveled off,"},{"time":108649,"text":"Pedro began leaving us,"},{"time":110934,"text":"and the beauty about it"},{"time":113147,"text":"is that I believe that there's something after life."},{"time":116979,"text":"You can see it in Pedro."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120273,"text":"[Danny Perasa to his wife Annie Perasa married 26 years]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":123849,"text":"Danny Perasa: See, the thing of it is,"},{"time":125579,"text":"I always feel guilty when I say \"I love you\" to you,"},{"time":128282,"text":"and I say it so often. I say it to remind you"},{"time":131174,"text":"that as dumpy as I am, it's coming from me,"},{"time":134228,"text":"it's like hearing a beautiful song from a busted old radio,"},{"time":138500,"text":"and it's nice of you to keep the radio around the house."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140625,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":142938,"text":"[Michael Wolmetz with his girlfriend Debora Brakarz]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":145638,"text":"Michael Wolmetz: So this is the ring that my father gave to my mother,"},{"time":148696,"text":"and we can leave it there."},{"time":150228,"text":"And he saved up and he purchased this,"},{"time":152036,"text":"and he proposed to my mother with this,"},{"time":153921,"text":"and so I thought that I would give it to you"},{"time":155862,"text":"so that he could be with us for this also."},{"time":159592,"text":"So I'm going to share a mic with you right now, Debora."},{"time":162950,"text":"Where's the right finger?"},{"time":164767,"text":"Debora Brakarz: (Crying)"},{"time":166540,"text":"MW: Debora, will you please marry me?"},{"time":170258,"text":"DB: Yes. Of course. I love you."},{"time":173697,"text":"(Kissing)"},{"time":176358,"text":"MW: So kids, this is how your mother and I got married,"},{"time":180919,"text":"in a booth in Grand Central Station with my father's ring."},{"time":184618,"text":"My grandfather was a cab driver for 40 years."},{"time":186752,"text":"He used to pick people up here every day."},{"time":188855,"text":"So it seems right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190982,"text":"Jake Barton: So I have to say"},{"time":192621,"text":"I did not actually choose those individual samples to make you cry"},{"time":195628,"text":"because they all make you cry."},{"time":197628,"text":"The entire project is predicated on this act of love"},{"time":200342,"text":"which is listening itself."},{"time":201893,"text":"And that motion of building an institution"},{"time":204678,"text":"out of a moment of conversation and listening"},{"time":206519,"text":"is actually a lot of what my firm, Local Projects,"},{"time":208371,"text":"is doing with our engagements in general."},{"time":211370,"text":"So we're a media design firm, and we're working"},{"time":213100,"text":"with a broad array of different institutions"},{"time":215249,"text":"building media installations for museums and public spaces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218482,"text":"Our latest engagement is the Cleveland Museum of Art,"},{"time":221158,"text":"which we've created an engagement called Gallery One for."},{"time":224238,"text":"And Gallery One is an interesting project"},{"time":226384,"text":"because it started with this massive, $350 million expansion"},{"time":230576,"text":"for the Cleveland Museum of Art,"},{"time":232055,"text":"and we actually brought in this piece"},{"time":234382,"text":"specifically to grow new capacity, new audiences,"},{"time":236885,"text":"at the same time that the museum itself is growing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239694,"text":"Glenn Lowry, the head of MoMA, put it best when he said,"},{"time":241898,"text":"\"We want visitors to actually cease being visitors."},{"time":244752,"text":"Visitors are transient. We want people who live here,"},{"time":246931,"text":"people who have ownership.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":248604,"text":"And so what we're doing is making a broad array"},{"time":250389,"text":"of different ways for people to actually engage"},{"time":252087,"text":"with the material inside of these galleries,"},{"time":254286,"text":"so you can still have a traditional gallery experience,"},{"time":257069,"text":"but if you're interested, you can actually engage"},{"time":259577,"text":"with any individual artwork and see the original context"},{"time":262378,"text":"from where it's from, or manipulate the work itself."},{"time":265120,"text":"So, for example, you can click on this individual lion head,"},{"time":267835,"text":"and this is where it originated from, 1300 B.C."},{"time":271109,"text":"Or this individual piece here,"},{"time":273219,"text":"you can see the actual bedroom. It really changes the way"},{"time":275734,"text":"you think about this type of a tempera painting."},{"time":279074,"text":"This is one of my favorites because you see the studio itself."},{"time":281572,"text":"This is Rodin's bust. You get the sense"},{"time":283417,"text":"of this incredible factory for creativity."},{"time":285885,"text":"And it makes you think about literally the hundreds"},{"time":287717,"text":"or thousands of years of human creativity and how"},{"time":290312,"text":"each individual artwork stands in for part of that story."},{"time":293367,"text":"This is Picasso,"},{"time":294658,"text":"of course embodying so much of it from the 20th century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297636,"text":"And so our next interface, which I'll show you,"},{"time":299937,"text":"actually leverages that idea of this lineage of creativity."},{"time":303120,"text":"It's an algorithm that actually allows you to browse"},{"time":306738,"text":"the actual museum's collection using facial recognition."},{"time":309937,"text":"So this person's making different faces,"},{"time":311863,"text":"and it's actually drawing forth different objects"},{"time":314270,"text":"from the collection that connect with exactly how she's looking."},{"time":317510,"text":"And so you can imagine that, as people are performing"},{"time":321555,"text":"inside of the museum itself, you get this sense"},{"time":324085,"text":"of this emotional connection,"},{"time":325085,"text":"this way in which our face connects with the thousands"},{"time":327438,"text":"and tens of thousands of years."},{"time":329351,"text":"This is an interface that actually allows you to draw"},{"time":331546,"text":"and then draws forth objects using those same shapes."},{"time":335490,"text":"So more and more we're trying to find ways"},{"time":337155,"text":"for people to actually author things inside of the museums themselves,"},{"time":340241,"text":"to be creative even as they're looking"},{"time":342241,"text":"at other people's creativity and understanding them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344929,"text":"So in this wall, the collections wall,"},{"time":347250,"text":"you can actually see all 3,000 artworks all at the same time,"},{"time":350749,"text":"and you can actually author your own"},{"time":352625,"text":"individual walking tours of the museum, so you can share them,"},{"time":355990,"text":"and someone can take a tour with the museum director"},{"time":358792,"text":"or a tour with their little cousin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361022,"text":"But all the while that we've been working"},{"time":362112,"text":"on this engagement for Cleveland,"},{"time":364250,"text":"we've also been working in the background"},{"time":365685,"text":"on really our largest engagement to date,"},{"time":367686,"text":"and that's the 9/11 Memorial and Museum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371270,"text":"So we started in 2006"},{"time":373879,"text":"as part of a team with Thinc Design"},{"time":376423,"text":"to create the original master plan for the museum,"},{"time":378920,"text":"and then we've done all the media design"},{"time":380620,"text":"both for the museum and the memorial and then the media production."},{"time":383207,"text":"So the memorial opened in 2011,"},{"time":386077,"text":"and the museum's going to open next year in 2014."},{"time":388602,"text":"And you can see from these images,"},{"time":389886,"text":"the site is so raw and almost archaeological."},{"time":393494,"text":"And of course the event itself is so recent,"},{"time":395468,"text":"somewhere between history and current events,"},{"time":398220,"text":"it was a huge challenge to imagine"},{"time":399703,"text":"how do you actually live up to a space like this,"},{"time":402653,"text":"an event like this, to actually tell that story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404847,"text":"And so what we started with"},{"time":406860,"text":"was really a new way of thinking about building an institution,"},{"time":410491,"text":"through a project called Make History,"},{"time":411998,"text":"which we launched in 2009."},{"time":413833,"text":"So it's estimated that a third of the world"},{"time":416766,"text":"watched 9/11 live,"},{"time":418446,"text":"and a third of the world"},{"time":419769,"text":"heard about it within 24 hours,"},{"time":421248,"text":"making it really by nature of when it happened,"},{"time":423616,"text":"this unprecedented moment of global awareness."},{"time":426816,"text":"And so we launched this to capture the stories"},{"time":429107,"text":"from all around the world,"},{"time":430210,"text":"through video, through photos,"},{"time":431876,"text":"through written history,"},{"time":433053,"text":"and so people's experiences on that day,"},{"time":434777,"text":"which was, in fact, this huge risk for the institution"},{"time":436843,"text":"to make its first move this open platform."},{"time":439312,"text":"But that was coupled together with this oral histories booth,"},{"time":442270,"text":"really the simplest we've ever made,"},{"time":443387,"text":"where you locate yourself on a map."},{"time":444515,"text":"It's in six languages, and you can tell your own story"},{"time":447091,"text":"about what happened to you on that day."},{"time":449103,"text":"And when we started seeing the incredible images"},{"time":452460,"text":"and stories that came forth"},{"time":453908,"text":"from all around the world --"},{"time":455177,"text":"this is obviously part of the landing gear --"},{"time":457249,"text":"we really started to understand"},{"time":459438,"text":"that there was this amazing symmetry"},{"time":461523,"text":"between the event itself,"},{"time":463046,"text":"between the way that people were telling the stories of the event,"},{"time":465345,"text":"and how we ourselves needed to tell that story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468641,"text":"This image in particular really captured"},{"time":470795,"text":"our attention at the time,"},{"time":471976,"text":"because it so much sums up that event."},{"time":474464,"text":"This is a shot from the Brooklyn-Battery Tunnel."},{"time":477071,"text":"There's a firefighter that's stuck, actually, in traffic,"},{"time":480200,"text":"and so the firefighters themselves are running"},{"time":483028,"text":"a mile and a half to the site itself"},{"time":484637,"text":"with upwards of 70 pounds of gear on their back."},{"time":487607,"text":"And we got this amazing email that said,"},{"time":490400,"text":"\"While viewing the thousands of photos on the site,"},{"time":492238,"text":"I unexpectedly found a photo of my son."},{"time":495211,"text":"It was a shock emotionally, yet a blessing to find this photo,\""},{"time":498171,"text":"and he was writing because he said,"},{"time":499492,"text":"\"I'd like to personally thank the photographer"},{"time":501832,"text":"for posting the photo,"},{"time":502981,"text":"as it meant more than words can describe to me"},{"time":505083,"text":"to have access to what is probably"},{"time":506876,"text":"the last photo ever taken of my son.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":511319,"text":"And it really made us recognize"},{"time":513620,"text":"what this institution needed to be"},{"time":516221,"text":"in order to actually tell that story."},{"time":518591,"text":"We can't have just a historian or a curator narrating"},{"time":522387,"text":"objectively in the third person about an event like that,"},{"time":525634,"text":"when you have the witnesses to history"},{"time":528164,"text":"who are going to make their way"},{"time":529010,"text":"through the actual museum itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532155,"text":"And so we started imagining the museum,"},{"time":534028,"text":"along with the creative team at the museum and the curators,"},{"time":537400,"text":"thinking about how the first voice that you would hear"},{"time":539297,"text":"inside the museum would actually be of other visitors."},{"time":541906,"text":"And so we created this idea of an opening gallery"},{"time":544394,"text":"called We Remember."},{"time":545831,"text":"And I'll just play you part of a mockup of it,"},{"time":547656,"text":"but you get a sense of what it's like to actually enter"},{"time":549603,"text":"into that moment in time"},{"time":550866,"text":"and be transported back in history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554119,"text":"(Video) Voice 1: I was in Honolulu, Hawaii.\nVoice 2: I was in Cairo, Egypt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557930,"text":"Voice 3: Sur les Champs-Élysées, à Paris.\nVoice 4: In college, at U.C. Berkeley."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561368,"text":"Voice 5: I was in Times Square.\nVoice 6: São Paolo, Brazil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564574,"text":"(Multiple voices)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":569190,"text":"Voice 7: It was probably about 11 o'clock at night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571986,"text":"Voice 8: I was driving to work at 5:45 local time in the morning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575734,"text":"Voice 9: We were actually in a meeting"},{"time":576995,"text":"when someone barged in and said,"},{"time":578722,"text":"\"Oh my God, a plane has just crashed into the World Trade Center.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":582515,"text":"Voice 10: Trying to frantically get to a radio."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584690,"text":"Voice 11: When I heard it over the radio --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":586119,"text":"Voice 12: Heard it on the radio."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587495,"text":"(Multiple voices)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":589245,"text":"Voice 13: I got a call from my father.\nVoice 14: The phone rang, it woke me up."},{"time":592179,"text":"My business partner told me to turn on the television."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594120,"text":"Voice 15: So I switched on the television."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596489,"text":"Voice 16: All channels in Italy were displaying the same thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598877,"text":"Voice 17: The Twin Towers.\nVoice 18: The Twin Towers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601719,"text":"JB: And you move from there"},{"time":602816,"text":"into that open, cavernous space."},{"time":604900,"text":"This is the so-called slurry wall."},{"time":606785,"text":"It's the original, excavated wall at the base of the World Trade Center"},{"time":609959,"text":"that withstood the actual pressure from the Hudson River"},{"time":612961,"text":"for a full year after the event itself."},{"time":614998,"text":"And so we thought about carrying that sense of authenticity,"},{"time":618199,"text":"of presence of that moment"},{"time":620574,"text":"into the actual exhibition itself."},{"time":622099,"text":"And we tell the stories of being inside the towers"},{"time":624849,"text":"through that same audio collage,"},{"time":626383,"text":"so you're hearing people literally talking about"},{"time":628350,"text":"seeing the planes as they make their way into the building,"},{"time":631274,"text":"or making their way down the stairwells."},{"time":633377,"text":"And as you make your way into the exhibition"},{"time":635624,"text":"where it talks about the recovery,"},{"time":637470,"text":"we actually project directly onto these moments"},{"time":639958,"text":"of twisted steel all of the experiences from people"},{"time":643155,"text":"who literally excavated on top of the pile itself."},{"time":646490,"text":"And so you can hear oral histories --"},{"time":648494,"text":"so people who were actually working the so-called bucket brigades"},{"time":650965,"text":"as you're seeing literally the thousands of experiences"},{"time":654150,"text":"from that moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655985,"text":"And as you leave that storytelling moment"},{"time":657839,"text":"understanding about 9/11,"},{"time":659702,"text":"we then turn the museum back into a moment of listening"},{"time":662750,"text":"and actually talk to the individual visitors"},{"time":665522,"text":"and ask them their own experiences about 9/11."},{"time":668153,"text":"And we ask them questions that are actually"},{"time":669370,"text":"not really answerable, the types of questions"},{"time":671408,"text":"that 9/11 itself draws forth for all of us."},{"time":674904,"text":"And so these are questions like,"},{"time":676326,"text":"\"How can a democracy balance freedom and security?\""},{"time":679483,"text":"\"How could 9/11 have happened?\""},{"time":683057,"text":"\"And how did the world change after 9/11?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":685192,"text":"And so these oral histories,"},{"time":686723,"text":"which we've actually been capturing already for years,"},{"time":689606,"text":"are then mixed together with interviews"},{"time":691745,"text":"that we're doing with people like Donald Rumsfeld,"},{"time":693971,"text":"Bill Clinton, Rudy Giuliani,"},{"time":695843,"text":"and you mix together these different players"},{"time":697963,"text":"and these different experiences,"},{"time":698994,"text":"these different reflection points about 9/11."},{"time":701360,"text":"And suddenly the institution, once again,"},{"time":703055,"text":"turns into a listening experience."},{"time":705396,"text":"So I'll play you just a short excerpt"},{"time":707217,"text":"of a mockup that we made of a couple of these voices,"},{"time":709171,"text":"but you really get a sense"},{"time":710968,"text":"of the poetry of everyone's reflection on the event."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714915,"text":"(Video) Voice 1: 9/11 was not just a New York experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718258,"text":"Voice 2: It's something that we shared, and it's something that united us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722268,"text":"Voice 3: And I knew when I saw that,"},{"time":723822,"text":"people who were there that day who immediately"},{"time":725877,"text":"went to help people known and unknown to them"},{"time":728937,"text":"was something that would pull us through."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730955,"text":"Voice 4: All the outpouring of affection and emotion"},{"time":733774,"text":"that came from our country was something really"},{"time":735742,"text":"that will forever, ever stay with me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738560,"text":"Voice 5: Still today I pray and think about those"},{"time":740306,"text":"who lost their lives,"},{"time":741995,"text":"and those who gave their lives to help others,"},{"time":744672,"text":"but I'm also reminded of the fabric of this country,"},{"time":748091,"text":"the love, the compassIon, the strength,"},{"time":750411,"text":"and I watched a nation come together"},{"time":752840,"text":"in the middle of a terrible tragedy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758013,"text":"JB: And so as people make their way out of the museum,"},{"time":760720,"text":"reflecting on the experience, reflecting on their own thoughts of it,"},{"time":763808,"text":"they then move into the actual space of the memorial itself,"},{"time":766984,"text":"because they've gone back up to grade,"},{"time":769062,"text":"and we actually got involved in the memorial"},{"time":771129,"text":"after we'd done the museum for a few years."},{"time":773368,"text":"The original designer of the memorial, Michael Arad,"},{"time":776177,"text":"had this image in his mind of all the names appearing"},{"time":778707,"text":"undifferentiated, almost random,"},{"time":781103,"text":"really a poetic reflection on top of the nature"},{"time":784935,"text":"of a terrorism event itself,"},{"time":786452,"text":"but it was a huge challenge for the families, for the foundation,"},{"time":789560,"text":"certainly for the first responders,"},{"time":791436,"text":"and there was a negotiation that went forth"},{"time":793566,"text":"and a solution was found"},{"time":795079,"text":"to actually create not an order in terms of chronology,"},{"time":798442,"text":"or in terms of alphabetical,"},{"time":799806,"text":"but through what's called meaningful adjacency."},{"time":801952,"text":"So these are groupings of the names themselves"},{"time":804703,"text":"which appear undifferentiated but actually have an order,"},{"time":807371,"text":"and we, along with Jer Thorp, created an algorithm"},{"time":810607,"text":"to take massive amounts of data"},{"time":812602,"text":"to actually start to connect together all these different names themselves."},{"time":815927,"text":"So this is an image of the actual algorithm itself"},{"time":818959,"text":"with the names scrambled for privacy,"},{"time":821315,"text":"but you can see that these blocks of color"},{"time":823695,"text":"are actually the four different flights,"},{"time":825645,"text":"the two different towers, the first responders,"},{"time":828422,"text":"and you can actually see within that different floors,"},{"time":830994,"text":"and then the green lines are the interpersonal connections"},{"time":833785,"text":"that were requested by the families themselves."},{"time":836959,"text":"And so when you go to the memorial,"},{"time":839340,"text":"you can actually see the overarching organization"},{"time":841990,"text":"inside of the individual pools themselves."},{"time":844874,"text":"You can see the way that the geography of the event"},{"time":847244,"text":"is reflected inside of the memorial,"},{"time":850127,"text":"and you can search for an individual name,"},{"time":851955,"text":"or in this case an employer, Cantor Fitzgerald,"},{"time":854530,"text":"and see the way in which all of those names,"},{"time":856926,"text":"those hundreds of names, are actually organized"},{"time":859036,"text":"onto the memorial itself,"},{"time":860728,"text":"and use that to navigate the memorial."},{"time":863346,"text":"And more importantly, when you're actually at the site"},{"time":865282,"text":"of the memorial, you can see those connections."},{"time":866761,"text":"You can see the relationships between the different names themselves."},{"time":870381,"text":"So suddenly what is this undifferentiated, anonymous"},{"time":873650,"text":"group of names springs into reality as an individual life."},{"time":878328,"text":"In this case, Harry Ramos,"},{"time":880496,"text":"who was the head trader at an investment bank,"},{"time":882835,"text":"who stopped to aid Victor Wald on the 55th floor of the South Tower."},{"time":887873,"text":"And Ramos told Wald, according to witnesses,"},{"time":890558,"text":"\"I'm not going to leave you.\""},{"time":893028,"text":"And Wald's widow requested that they be listed next to each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":898604,"text":"Three generations ago, we had to actually get people"},{"time":901806,"text":"to go out and capture the stories for common people."},{"time":905203,"text":"Today, of course, there's an unprecedented amount of stories"},{"time":908671,"text":"for all of us that are being captured for future generations."},{"time":912569,"text":"And this is our hope, that's there's poetry inside of each of our stories."}]},{"cues":[{"time":916097,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":917021,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}